<subSubSection id="C36CC293FFB9FF9EFF20F9D1FE7BF8F2" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20F9D1FC3FF9DA" blockId="1.[151,1437,1482,2013]" box="[199,991,1554,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFF20F9D1FEB9F9DB" bold="true" box="[199,345,1554,1580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Description.</emphasis>
Similar in appearance to other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFCC9F9D0FC38F9DA" authorityName="Zakhvatkin" authorityYear="1953" box="[814,984,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFCC9F9D0FC38F9DA" box="[814,984,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Mongolojassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20F9F4FC3DF94A" blockId="1.[151,1437,1482,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
Aedeagal processes in posterior view at bases bent basad and diverging at angle slightly less than 90 
<superScript id="7C033C50FFB9FF9EFAB5F9F4FABAF9B2" attach="none" box="[1362,1370,1591,1605]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">o</superScript>
, with small additional branches before midlength, and with tips bent outwards (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFC04F998FBD9F981" box="[995,1081,1627,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Length of processes does not exceeds one third of shaft length. Aedeagal shaft slightly S-curved in lateral view, with processes almost parallel to distal part of shaft (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFE96F960FE1AF94A" box="[369,506,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Figs. 17–18</figureCitation>
), not narrowed beyond gonopore (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFC9BF960FC2FF94A" box="[892,975,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20F904FE7BF8F2" blockId="1.[151,1437,1482,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFE94F904FE18F916" baseAuthorityName="Horvath" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[371,504,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFE94F904FE18F916" box="[371,504,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and differs from it only in diverging aedeagal processes (more or less parallel in 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFA99F904FF17F8F2" baseAuthorityName="Horvath" baseAuthorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFA99F904FF17F8F2" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFB9FF9EFEE1F928FE70F8F2" box="[262,400,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Figs. 22–23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CC293FFB9FF9EFF20F8CDFC72F8B9" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20F8CDFC72F8B9" blockId="1.[151,1437,1482,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFF20F8CDFE81F8DF" bold="true" box="[199,353,1806,1832]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Distribution.</emphasis>
Northern part of European 
<collectingCountry id="F361D188FFB9FF9EFD47F8CCFD0BF8DE" box="[672,747,1807,1833]" name="Russia" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFB9FF9EFD1CF8CCFC03F8DE" author="Ossiannilsson, F." box="[763,995,1807,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" pagination="594 - 979" refId="ref4089" refString="Ossiannilsson, F. (1983) The Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Part 3: The Family Cicadellidae: Deltocephalinae, Catalogue, Literature and Index. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 7, 594 - 979." type="journal article" year="1983">Ossiannilsson, 1983</bibRefCitation>
