<collectingRegion id="49B25FFAFFB9FF9EFE24F8F0FE1BF8BA" box="[451,507,1843,1869]" country="Russia" name="Altay" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Altai</collectingRegion>
Mts., Western Siberia (new record).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36CC293FFB9FF9BFF20F894FB6AFE5A" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="578" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9EFF20F894FF09F862" blockId="1.[151,1437,1482,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFF20F894FEDBF886" bold="true" box="[199,315,1879,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Remarks.</emphasis>
A comprehensive illustrated description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFCB1F894FBF1F886" baseAuthorityName="J. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[854,1041,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicuspidatus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFCB1F894FBF1F886" box="[854,1041,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">M. bicuspidatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFB9FF9EFAE6F894FF06F862" author="Ossiannilsson, F." pageId="1" pageNumber="575" pagination="594 - 979" refId="ref4089" refString="Ossiannilsson, F. (1983) The Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Part 3: The Family Cicadellidae: Deltocephalinae, Catalogue, Literature and Index. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 7, 594 - 979." type="journal article" year="1983">Ossiannilsson (1983)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFB9FF9BFF20F85CFEAFFF22" blockId="1.[151,1437,1482,2013]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="578" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFB9FF9EFF20F85CFE99F84E" author="Mityaev, I. D." box="[199,377,1951,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" pagination="1 - 170" refId="ref4050" refString="Mityaev, I. D. (2002) Fauna, ecology, and zoogeography of leafhoppers (Homoptera, Cicadinea) of Kazakhstan. Tethys Entomological Research, 5, 1 - 170. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2002">Mityaev (2002)</bibRefCitation>
treats 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFE2EF85CFDB1F84E" baseAuthorityName="Horvath" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[457,593,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFE2EF85CFDB1F84E" box="[457,593,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFB9FF9EFC88F85CFBC5F84E" baseAuthorityName="J. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[879,1061,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicuspidatus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFB9FF9EFC88F85CFBC5F84E" box="[879,1061,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">M. bicuspidatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and points out that this taxon is widespread in the steppe zone of Northern, Central, and Eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F361D188FFB9FF9EFC85F800FC08F82A" box="[866,1000,1987,2013]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="1" pageNumber="575">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
. However, in his keys for identification of Auchenorrhyncha of 
<collectingCountry id="F361D188FFBCFF9BFE47FF54FDC3FF46" box="[416,547,151,177]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFDD6FF54FD36FF46" author="Mityaev, I. D." box="[561,726,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" refId="ref4015" refString="Mityaev, I. D. (1971) Cicadinea of Kazakhstan. Keys for identification of species. &quot; Nauka &quot; Publ., Alma-Ata, 211 pp. [in Rus- sian]" type="book" year="1971">Mityaev, 1971</bibRefCitation>
), he gives drawings of the aedeagus of a typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFB17FF54FA95FF46" baseAuthorityName="Horvath" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1264,1397,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFB17FF54FA95FF46" box="[1264,1397,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as on 
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFF5DFF78FEA3FF22" box="[186,323,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figs. 22–23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF09C190FFBAFF9DFF70F8A9FE7DF819" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480090" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6480090" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480090/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" startId="2.[151,264,1898,1922]" targetBox="[201,1385,187,1865]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBAFF9DFF70F8A9FE7DF819" blockId="2.[151,1437,1898,2030]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBAFF9DFF70F8A9FEA7F875" bold="true" box="[151,327,1898,1922]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">FIGURES 1–15.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBAFF9DFEAAF8A9FDBCF875" authority="Tishechkin, 2022" authorityName="Tishechkin" authorityYear="2022" box="[333,604,1898,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBAFF9DFEAAF8A9FDBCF875" box="[333,604,1898,1922]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">Mongolojassus caucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBAFF9DFD85F8A9FD7BF875" bold="true" box="[610,667,1898,1922]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A231F071FFBAFF9DFD85F8A9FD7BF875" box="[610,667,1898,1922]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(1–14) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBAFF9DFCF2F8A8FC50F875" baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[789,944,1898,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="servadeinus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBAFF9DFCF2F8A8FC50F875" box="[789,944,1898,1922]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="576">M. servadeinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(15). 1―male, dorsal habitus, 2―same, female, 3―pygofer, lateral view, 4―same, ventral view, 5― subgenital plates, valve, connective, styles, and aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–8, 15―aedeagus, back view, 9―same, apical part, 10–12―same, lateral view, 13–14―posterior and lateral view. 15―after 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBAFF9DFF70F815FE79F819" author="D'Urso, V. &amp; Remane, R." box="[151,409,2006,2030]" pageId="2" pageNumber="576" pagination="35 - 48" refId="ref3557" refString="D'Urso, V. &amp; Remane, R. (1994) Remarks on some separated, peripheric and relictary West European populations of the Asiatic genus Mongolojassus Zakhvatkin: taxonomy and distribution. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 72, 35 - 48." type="journal article" year="1994">D’Urso &amp; Remane, 1994</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF09C190FFBBFF9CFF70F885FCEFF819" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="577" startId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" targetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBBFF9CFF70F885FCEFF819" blockId="3.[151,1437,1862,2030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="577">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBBFF9CFF70F885FEB6F8A9" bold="true" box="[151,342,1862,1886]" pageId="3" pageNumber="577">FIGURES 16–34.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBBFF9CFEB9F885FDCBF8A9" box="[350,555,1862,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBBFF9CFEB9F885FE17F8A9" box="[350,503,1862,1886]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="577">Mongolojassus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
16–21― 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBBFF9CFD6CF884FCCFF8A9" baseAuthorityName="J. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[651,815,1862,1886]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicuspidatus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBBFF9CFD6CF884FCCFF8A9" box="[651,815,1862,1886]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="577">M. bicuspidatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from Northern Europe, after 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBBFF9CFEAEF8A9FDF9F875" author="Ossiannilsson, F." box="[329,537,1898,1922]" pageId="3" pageNumber="577" pagination="594 - 979" refId="ref4089" refString="Ossiannilsson, F. (1983) The Auchenorrhyncha (Homoptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Part 3: The Family Cicadellidae: Deltocephalinae, Catalogue, Literature and Index. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica, 7, 594 - 979." type="journal article" year="1983">Ossiannilsson, 1983</bibRefCitation>
), 22–23― 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBBFF9CFD63F8A8FD1DF875" baseAuthorityName="Horvath" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[644,765,1898,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBBFF9CFD63F8A8FD1DF875" box="[644,765,1898,1922]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="577">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(after 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBBFF9CFCA6F8A9FBE2F875" author="Emelyanov, A. F." box="[833,1026,1898,1922]" pageId="3" pageNumber="577" pagination="626 - 632" refId="ref3603" refString="Emelyanov, A. F. (1964 a) New species of steppe leafhoppers (Homoptera, Cicadellidae) from Transbaikalia and other eastern regions of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 43 (3), 626 - 632. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Emelyanov, 1964a</bibRefCitation>
), 24–31― 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBBFF9CFB8BF8A8FB19F875" authorityName="Emelyanov" authorityYear="1976" box="[1132,1273,1898,1922]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vinokurovi">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBBFF9CFB8BF8A8FB19F875" box="[1132,1273,1898,1922]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="577">M. vinokurovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBBFF9CFD29F84DFC64F851" author="Emelyanov, A. F." box="[718,900,1934,1958]" pageId="3" pageNumber="577" pagination="357 - 363" refId="ref3719" refString="Emelyanov, A. F. (1976) New genera and species of leafhoppers (Homoptera, Auchenorrhyncha) from North-East of the USSR. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 55 (2), 357 - 363. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1976">Emelyanov, 1976</bibRefCitation>
), 32–34― 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBBFF9CFC17F84CFB67F851" baseAuthorityName="Zakhvatkin" baseAuthorityYear="1953" box="[1008,1159,1934,1958]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elpatjevskii">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBBFF9CFC17F84CFB67F851" box="[1008,1159,1934,1958]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="577">M. elpatjevskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC99118FFBCFF9BFF20FF1CFB6AFE5A" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFF20FF1CFE9DFF0E" baseAuthorityName="J. Sahlberg" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[199,381,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicuspidatus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFF20FF1CFE9DFF0E" box="[199,381,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">M. bicuspidatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFE5EFF1CFDA1FF0E" baseAuthorityName="Horvath" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[441,577,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFE5EFF1CFDA1FF0E" box="[441,577,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are, apparently, fully sympatric, since 
<taxonomicName id="4C76EA9BFFBCFF9BFBE3FF1CFB6CFF0E" baseAuthorityName="Horvath" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1028,1164,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mongolojassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis id="B9024D0AFFBCFF9BFBE3FF1CFB6CFF0E" box="[1028,1164,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F361D188FFBCFF9BFA90FF1CFF2FFEEA" name="Estonia" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Estonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFF07FEC0FE69FEEA" author="Vilbaste, J." box="[224,393,258,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" refId="ref4176" refString="Vilbaste, J. (1965) On the fauna of Auchenorrhyncha of Altai. Akademiya Nauk Estonskoy SSR, Institut Zoologii i Botaniki, Tartu, 144 pp. [in Russian with German summary]" type="book" year="1965">Vilbaste, 1965</bibRefCitation>
), steppes of the Southeastern European 
<collectingCountry id="F361D188FFBCFF9BFCB1FEC0FC41FEEA" box="[854,929,259,285]" name="Russia" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFC55FEC0FB6CFEE9" author="Emelyanov, A. F." box="[946,1164,259,286]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" pagination="337 - 437" refId="ref3649" refString="Emelyanov, A. F. (1964 b) Suborder Cicadinea (Auchenorrhyncha). Keys to Species of Insects of the European Part of the USSR, 1, 337 - 437. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1964">Emelyanov, 1964b</bibRefCitation>
), the Urals (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFAFDFEC0FEB3FEB6" author="Galinichev, A. V. &amp; Anufriev, G. A." pageId="4" pageNumber="578" pagination="74 - 82" refId="ref3809" refString="Galinichev, A. V. &amp; Anufriev, G. A. (2012 a) On the fauna of leafhoppers (Homoptera, Cicadina) of the Nature Reserve and Museum &quot; Arkaim &quot; (Chelyabinsk Oblast). Aridnye Ecosystemy, 2 (15), 74 - 82. [in Russian with English summary] https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / S 2079096112020023" type="journal article" year="2012">Galinichev, Anufriev, 2012a</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingRegion id="49B25FFAFFBCFF9BFE81FEE4FE7EFEB6" box="[358,414,295,321]" country="Russia" name="Altay" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Altai</collectingRegion>
Mts. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFE0EFEE4FD71FEB6" author="Vilbaste, J." box="[489,657,294,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" refId="ref4176" refString="Vilbaste, J. (1965) On the fauna of Auchenorrhyncha of Altai. Akademiya Nauk Estonskoy SSR, Institut Zoologii i Botaniki, Tartu, 144 pp. [in Russian with German summary]" type="book" year="1965">Vilbaste, 1965</bibRefCitation>
), and the steppe zone of 
<collectingCountry id="F361D188FFBCFF9BFC57FEE4FBD3FEB6" box="[944,1075,295,321]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE7ECE9FFBCFF9BFBA5FEE4FB0BFEB6" author="Mityaev, I. D." box="[1090,1259,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="578" refId="ref4015" refString="Mityaev, I. D. (1971) Cicadinea of Kazakhstan. Keys for identification of species. &quot; Nauka &quot; Publ., Alma-Ata, 211 pp. [in Rus- sian]" type="book" year="1971">Mityaev, 1971</bibRefCitation>
). Still, we have not seen males with traits intermediate between these two species. On the contrary, aedeagus shape in males from distant localities is remarkably similar (
<figureCitation id="134D8D9DFFBCFF9BFDAAFEACFCB1FE7E" box="[589,849,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–34" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[230,1357,184,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-28@3.[221,1366,181,1838]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 16–34. Mongolojassus spp. 16–21―M. bicuspidatus (16–19―males from Altai Mts., 20–21―male from North- ern Europe, after Ossiannilsson, 1983), 22–23―M. sibiricus (after Emelyanov, 1964a), 24–31―M. vinokurovi (24–28―males from Irkutsk Oblast, 29–31―male from Yakutia, after Emelyanov, 1976), 32–34―M. elpatjevskii (32–33―female holotype, 34―male paratype). 16, 20, 22, 24–25, 29―aedeagus, posterior view, 19, 28, 31―same, apical part, 17–18, 21, 23, 26–27, 30―same, lateral view, 32, 34―habitus, 33―holotype labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6480092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6480092/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="578">Figs. 16–17 and 20–21</figureCitation>
). Thus, investigation of genitalia variability based on numerous materials from different localities is necessary to clarify the status of these taxa.
</paragraph>
